President Biden welcomed Chancellor Scholz to the Oval Office, stating that Germany is one of America's closest allies. They discussed working together to deter Russian aggression in Europe, address challenges posed by China, promote stability in the Western Balkans, and tackle issues such as the pandemic and climate change. Chancellor Scholz expressed appreciation for the opportunity to discuss these important topics and emphasized the need for intense collaboration between the two countries. The meeting took place at a crucial time, particularly in light of Russian aggression against Ukraine.